text: Golden Swan-True American, also known as the Caola Building, is located in Trenton, Mercer County, New Jersey, United States. The building was built in 1861 and was added to the National Register of Historic Places on April 30, 2008. ==See also== *National Register of Historic Places listings in Mercer County, New Jersey ==References== Category:Commercial buildings on the National Register of Historic Places in New Jersey Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1861 Category:Buildings and structures in Trenton, New Jersey Category:National Register of Historic Places in Trenton, New Jersey Category:1861 establishments in New Jersey Category:New Jersey Register of Historic Places
title: Golden Swan-True American
